About Me

I'm currently a Senior at Stanford University majoring in American Studies with a focus on race, gender and sexuality in American media and entertainment. Additionally, I'm minoring in Creative Writing with an emphasis on screenwriting. My professional experience spans both scripted and unscripted television, working with development teams to create new and exciting shows. My experience spans the whole computing stack. From designing and building an FPGA ipod in verilog, to building a sign language interpreter using pytorch, I'm interested in using my engineering background to build novel technologies and products. I'm especially motivated by using technology to tackle challenging societal problems.
